Distinguished from closest known relative (
A. omayan
) by male clypeus modification ( Fig. 191 ; apophyses closer together), distinct ventro-distal apophysis on male palpal femur ( Fig. 190 ; only indistinct hump in
A. omayan
), and shape of epigynum ( Fig. 213 ; whitish areas smaller and wider apart). Distinguished from other congeners by bipartite retrolatero-ventral process on procursus ( Fig. 190 ), male palpal trochanter with prolateral apophysis ( Fig. 189 ; other species with only ventral apophysis), and pair of internal sclerotized pockets in female genitalia ( Figs 192–193 ).

Named for Philippine-born cosmopolitan artist Pacita Abad (
1946–2004
), famous for her vibrant, colorful abstract work, but also for her paintings of tropical flowers and animal wildlife.

Known from two localities on Negros Island only (
type
locality and nearby locality; 
Fig. 5
).
